headshotImage.longCaption: Umar Gul player page headshot cutout, 2021

commentTextItems.html: Sunny safely taps his first ball in ODI cricket down to point

commentPostTextItems.html: Nasir Hossain gives Bangladesh something to shout about in an otherwise sorry chase. Bangladesh weren't playing for a win after they lost four wickets. Their only realistic aim was to bat out 50 overs to see how much they could get. Better than a meek surrender. This may not have been the best advertisement for one-day cricket. Bangladesh needed to save face and draw some positives in defeat, so  you cannot fault their resilience. In the end they discovered a gritty player in Nasir Hossain. Hopefully he can bring out some consistent performances.
It could have been different had Pakistan taken their catches. Both Shakib and Nasir were dropped at least once, and the spinners for a change looked worn out. Rare off day for Afridi.
Pakistan take the series 2-0. Stay with us for the presentation.
Mushfiqur: "Special mention to Nasir. He showed us how to bat on this pitch. It;s time to play as a team."

Misbah: "The guys are doing a really good job. It wasn't the best track to bat on, the ball was gripping. Umar Akmal is an impact player. Both Hafeez and Afridi are really good allrounders.Gul's bowling well with the new ball. Really good to have allrounders in the team."
Nasir is the Man of the Match (Mushfiqur translates): "I am over the moon. There were a lot nof good bowlers in their side."
This was interesting because Nasir was trying to answer in English but Ramiz insisted he speak in Bengali!
That's it from us. The next game is on December 6 in Chittagong. Join us then. Thanks for your company and cheers!

fortuitous but he gets there! Chips down the track and gets an outside edge that beats the keeper, no slips, down to third man, at least Nasir goes home happy and well done to him!

dismissalText.long: c Nasir Hossain b Shafiul Islam
dismissalText.commentary: Imran Farhat c Nasir Hossain b Shafiul Islam 4 (4b 1x4 0x6 12m) SR: 100

dismissalComment.html: didn't take too long for Shafiul to get his man! He pitched it a bit shorter outside off and got it to angle across, lured Farhat into cutting, it was in the air and straight to backward point

headshotImage.longCaption: Imrul Kayes player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.long: c Imrul Kayes b Rubel Hossain
dismissalText.commentary: Mohammad Hafeez c Imrul Kayes b Rubel Hossain 32 (56b 6x4 0x6 81m) SR: 57.14

dismissalComment.html: change of pace, change of luck! Hafeez loses concentration and falls to a very poor shot, fetches a short ball from outside off and gets a top edge that swirls to Kayes at mid-on, easy one

headshotImage.caption: Abdur Razzak player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Abdur Razzak player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Younis Khan lbw b Abdur Razzak 37 (70b 3x4 0x6 96m) SR: 52.85

dismissalComment.html: trapped in front! Lands on middle and the ball straightens, Younis stays at the crease and is trapped as the ball skids through and hits him in line with the stumps, the ball straightened and that foxed him

headshotImage.caption: Shafiul Islam player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Shafiul Islam player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.long: c Shafiul Islam b Shakib Al Hasan
dismissalText.commentary: Umar Akmal c Shafiul Islam b Shakib Al Hasan 59 (54b 5x4 1x6 53m) SR: 109.25

dismissalComment.html: loose shot in the end, tossed up on the off stump, Umar makes room and lofts but it's a half-hearted loft, Shafiul takes the skier easily at long-off plenty of yards in front of the rope

headshotImage.longCaption: Elias Sunny player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.longCaption: Farhad Reza player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.long: c sub (Farhad Reza) b Elias Sunny
dismissalText.commentary: Misbah-ul-Haq c sub (Farhad Reza) b Elias Sunny 37 (55b 1x4 0x6 95m) SR: 67.27

dismissalComment.html: down the throat of long-on! Tossed up on middle, he makes a bit of room and tries to slam it down the ground but miscues it to Farhad (substitute), easily taken, that's the first ODI wicket for Sunny

headshotImage.caption: Shoaib Malik player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Shoaib Malik player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Shoaib Malik c †Mushfiqur Rahim b Rubel Hossain 17 (20b 2x4 0x6 32m) SR: 85

dismissalComment.html: Malik tries to get too cheeky, he tries to dab a slower delivery down to third man but ends up getting a big outside edge, no problem for Rahim, the umpire took a bit of time to raise the finger, it was obvious

headshotImage.caption: Shafiul Islam player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Shafiul Islam player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Shahid Afridi c Mahmudullah b Shafiul Islam 42 (27b 3x4 2x6 35m) SR: 155.55

dismissalComment.html: the slower ball foxes him, he clears the back leg and tries to heave him over the on side, top edge and Mahmudullah runs to short point and takes the catch

headshotImage.caption: Umar Gul player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Umar Gul player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.long: c Younis Khan b Umar Gul
dismissalText.commentary: Tamim Iqbal c Younis Khan b Umar Gul 4 (9b 0x4 0x6 13m) SR: 44.44

dismissalComment.html: Gul can thank his lucky stars he got a wicket with that, too wide outside, Tamim ought to have left it but he stayed at the crease and chased it, takes the outermost portion of the outside edge and Younis does really well to fall to his left and take it, Younis looks really amused

headshotImage.longCaption: Imrul Kayes player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.longCaption: Imrul Kayes player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Imrul Kayes c Misbah-ul-Haq b Mohammad Hafeez 6 (26b 0x4 0x6 26m) SR: 23.07

dismissalComment.html: and I obviously spoke too soon about Hafeez! Kayes tries to do something different to get out of the rut, tossed up outside off and he comes forward to drives on the up, tamely chips it to short cover

headshotImage.longCaption: Shahriar Nafees player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Shahriar Nafees lbw b Mohammad Hafeez 7 (8b 0x4 0x6 22m) SR: 87.5

dismissalComment.html: he gets him this time! Flatter delivery and Nafees prods forward to defend, wasn't too far from the inside edge but the umpire Cloete reckoned that was hitting the off stump

headshotImage.caption: Umar Gul player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Umar Gul player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.long: c Mohammad Hafeez b Umar Gul
dismissalText.commentary: Mushfiqur Rahim c Mohammad Hafeez b Umar Gul 1 (10b 0x4 0x6 12m) SR: 10

dismissalComment.html: another one bites the dust! Bit of extra bounce from Gul as he lands it outside off, Mushfiqur got beside the line but the ball flew off the shoulder of the bat down to Hafeez at gully. Hafeez has featured in the last three dismissals

dismissalComment.html: softest of dismissals, quite an irony considering the way he had been playing for the last hour, he shapes to pull against the turn, ends up giving catching practice to Ajmal
